=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_UGens-and-Synths_ex6 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 809 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, and filtered with steep_rolloff character.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: moderate
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 809.2956
  harmonic_decay_rate: -8.9148
  harmonic_regularity: 0.6623
  pitch_clarity: 101.6275
  inharmonicity: 0.0031
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -17.9443
  resonance_freq: 775.1953

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Unit Generators and Synths Example 6
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/UGens-and-Synths.html
// Tags: UGens-and-Synths, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 6 ---
FSinOsc.ar(800, 0.0, 0.2) + BrownNoise.ar(0.2); // press enter and look at the post window

{FSinOsc.ar(800, 0.0, 0.2) + BrownNoise.ar(0.2)}.play; // play it
